<subSubSection id="EA7D1F1ADA9EC6AB2EB9C7A1FE56EF93" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="35B994BD7198C405B11102B1B9B36515" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EE49E2291686E96584F7F8AAB7B37C51" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="659FB9E3C9D57D64BCEB3B542C72BC08" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="haenkeana">
<emphasis id="036ACE4329420373A9FA2AF4EC3600EE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea haenkeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most likely to be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="60212000F3996E609B84DD675CB49AA2" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cuneifolia">
<emphasis id="5BFFE42CC6A93A19BFC8C080587DD48C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. cuneifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which has narrower leaves and a much shorter, more compact, unbranched terminal inflorescence.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D81708B683182B3DE88C5EA8DD362257" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The cited type locality of 
<normalizedToken id="29D7E11750A91EE9244279329486B372" originalValue="“Cochabamba”">&quot;Cochabamba&quot;</normalizedToken>
must be wrong as this is a plant of lowland cerrado vegetation, not inter-Andean dry valleys.
</paragraph>
